  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375 degrees.",
    "In a blender, combine dashi extract, olive oil, garlic, ginger, cumin, paprika, salt, and black pepper, and blend until smooth.",
    "In a large bowl, toss the black olives with the blended mixture until they are evenly coated.",
    "Line a bamboo tray with parchment paper and arrange the olives in a single layer.",
    "Bake the olives for 20 minutes, or until crispy.",
    "Remove the olives from the oven and let them cool completely.",
    "Serve the crispy black olives in the bamboo tray.",
    "Garnish with fresh parsley or cilantro, if desired."
  ],
